A stream-based solution using [`Stream.noneMatch()`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/stream/Stream.html#noneMatch(java.util.function.Predicate)), this operation is *short-circuit* and exception would be thrown only if there are no active objects.

```
private static void validateAdvertisements(List&lt;Advertisement&gt; advertisements) {
    boolean isActiveNotFound = advertisements.stream()
        .noneMatch(Advertisement::isActive);
        
    if (isActiveNotFound) throw new NoAdvertisementAvailableException();
}
```
In case if `NoAdvertisementAvailableException` is a *runtime exception*, it can be propagated outside the functions implementing standard functional interfaces from the JDK, like `Runnable`.

Here&#39;s an example that makes use of the combination [`Stream.findFirst()`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/stream/Stream.html#findFirst()) + [`Optional.ifPresentOrElse()`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Optional.html#ifPresentOrElse(java.util.function.Consumer,java.lang.Runnable)):

```
private static void validateAdvertisements(List&lt;Advertisement&gt; advertisements) {
    advertisements.stream()
        .filter(Advertisement::isActive)
        .findFirst()
        .ifPresentOrElse(s -&gt; {},
            () -&gt; { throw new NoAdvertisementAvailableException(); }
    );
}
```

