Yes, Spring has a doc on getting [Async Query Results][1] via custom repository methods.  Basically, you can use the `@Async` annotation and then wrap the return type with one of the *Future types.

So in your case, `countByInstanceId` might look something like this:


    @Async
    ListenableFuture&lt;long&gt; countByInstanceId(String instanceId);

  [1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-data/jpa/docs/current/reference/html/#repositories.query-async

